Four stakeholders grounded in what I actually saw in the code: William (the researcher reading the git log), FLS spec readers (who care about ambiguity findings currently buried in inline comments), future contributors (who can infer the claims methodology from commits but find nothing that explains it), and CI/validation infrastructure. The tensions are real ones I found: parse fixtures vs. full pipeline codegen, breadth vs. correctness depth (the assembly inspection gap), and ambiguity documentation vs. forward progress.

